OL,3,COmagh Bomb Inquiry ask Government to
OL,4,Cdetail civil servant risk
OL,6,FThe Government has been asked to
OL,7,Furgently inform the Omagh Bombing
OL,8,FInquiry if any civil servants have
OL,9,Fbeen put at risk because their names
OL,10,Fare on documents given to the probe.
OL,12,FThe inquiry has been sitting in
OL,13,FBelfast to hear a government
OL,14,Fapplication for the identities of
OL,15,Fjunior civil servants to be blanked
OL,16,Fout.
OL,18,FIt's emerged that 700 documents
OL,19,Fcontaining up to 8000 pages can't be
OL,20,Fdisclosed to other participants due to
OL,21,Fissues surrounding redactions.
